    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-09-06T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-06T23:00:00-05:00" n="649"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-07T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1920—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 7—6:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>243. Williams<note n="20" xml:id="d649fn20">Charles L. L. Williams, formerly of
                        U.S. consular service.</note> advises he assumed office of associate
                    inspector general Wine, Tobacco September 1st. States that, pending formal
                    establishment [of] inspectorate general and to facilitate collection [of]
                    necessary data, he has been instructed as tentative measure to finance [<hi
                        rend="italic">function?</hi>] under orders [of] Premier and Minister of
                    Finance. Copies of all reports, accounts and returns necessary for full
                    investigation of the revenue concerned will be furnished by [<hi rend="italic"
                        >to?</hi>] him.</p>
                <pb facs="0757" n="659" xml:id="pg_659"/>
                <p>Legation has not received reply from the Chinese Government regarding extension
                    of option Pacific Development Corporation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
